{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "End user-centric longitudinal studies can produce valuable insights into the usability and adoption of explainable social media recommendation systems (Gjoreski et al., 2024; Hamm et al., 2023).",
    "Moreover, exploring the end users' explanation perception by presenting them with various explanation formats and dimensions can be eyeopening regarding users' explanation requirements (Eagly & Chaiken, 1993; Fazio & Olson, 2007; Wixom & Todd, 2005).",
    "Future studies can explore the end users' perception of users in other age groups and literacy levels, which can also be a valuable contribution to AI literacy (Hamm et al., 2023; Wang et al., 2023).",
    "Finally, in this study, we have proposed a framework for developing explainable social media systems that adopts the concept of design science research (Cirqueira et al., 2021; Hevner et al., 2004; Peffers et al., 2007).",
    "Evaluation of this framework can also shed light on the XAI design and development."
  ],
